  "response_text": "Here's a daily fitness routine that you can follow:\n\n**Warm-up (10-15 minutes)**\n\n1. Light cardio: Jumping jacks, jogging in place, or cycling\n2. Dynamic stretching: Leg swings, arm circles, hip circles, and torso twists\n\n**Monday (Upper Body Workout)**\n\n1. Push-ups: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n2. Bicep curls: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Tricep dips: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Shoulder press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n\n**Tuesday (Lower Body Workout)**\n\n1. Squats: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n2. Lunges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (per leg)\n3. Calf raises: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n4. Leg press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Glute bridges: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n\n**Wednesday (Rest Day or Active Recovery)**\n\n* Take a rest day or engage in light activities like yoga, walking, or swimming\n\n**Thursday (Core Workout)**\n\n1. Crunches: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n2. Russian twists: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Leg raises: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Bicycle crunches: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n\n**Friday (Upper Body Workout)**\n\n1. Incline push-ups: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n2. Incline dumbbell press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n3. Lateral raises: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n4. Rear delt fly: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Tricep extensions: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n\n**Saturday (Lower Body Workout)**\n\n1. Deadlifts: 3 sets of 8-10 reps\n2. Step-ups: 3 sets of 10-12 reps (per leg)\n3. Calf raises: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n4. Leg press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n5. Glute bridges: 3 sets of 12-15 reps\n\n**Sunday (Rest Day or Active Recovery)**\n\n* Take a rest day or engage in light activities like yoga, walking, or swimming\n\n**Additional Tips**\n\n1. Start with lighter weights and gradually increase the intensity as you get stronger.\n2. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets, and 120-180 seconds between exercises.\n3. Stay hydrated and fuel your body with a balanced diet.\n4. Listen to your body and take rest days as needed.\n5. Mix up your routine every 4-6 weeks to avoid plateaus and prevent overuse injuries.\n\nRemember, consistency and patience are key. Stick to your routine and make adjustments as needed to achieve your fitness goals.",
